#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:41
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:38
msgid "Burn"
msgstr "加深"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:43
msgid ""
"An image-wide burn-filter. Burn is named after a trick in traditional dark-"
"room photography that gave similar results."
msgstr "用來把影像加深的濾鏡。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:59
msgid "Levels"
msgstr "色階"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:61
msgid ""
"This filter allows you to directly modify the levels of the tone-values of "
"an image, by manipulating sliders for highlights, midtones and shadows. You "
"can even set an output and input range of tones for the image. A histogram "
"is displayed to show you the tonal distribution. The default shortcut for "
"levels filter is :kbd:`Ctrl + L`."
msgstr ""
"這個濾鏡可以直接調整影像中的明度，以控制滑條的方式來調整高亮色，中間色和陰影"
"色的明度。你甚至能夠分別調整輸入和輸出時的色階。視窗中有著顯示色調分布的直方"
"圖。色階預設的快捷鍵是 :kbd:`Ctrl + L`\\ 。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:66
msgid ""
"With these two buttons you can switch between \"lightness only\" and \"per "
"channel\" levels adjustment. If you use the second mode you can modify the "
"levels for each channel independently and you can change the active channel "
"by selecting it in the list that appears at the right side of the buttons."
msgstr ""
"這兩個按鈕可以切換「僅亮度」和「每通道」的色階調整。當你使用第二個模式時，你"
"可以獨立調整每個色彩通道，然後你可以在按鈕右邊的選單更改目前所啓用的通道。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:67
msgid "This area shows the histogram for the active channel."
msgstr "這個區域會顯示已啟用色彩通道的直方圖。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:68
msgid ""
"This is a slider that you can use to quickly change the input black and "
"white points and gamma."
msgstr "這個滑條可以有效地調整輸入色彩的黑白點值及 Gamma。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:69
msgid ""
"These input boxes do the same as the input levels slider, but allow you to "
"finetune the values."
msgstr "這個輸入框的功能和輸入色彩滑條相同，不過你可以透過輸入框來精確地調整數值。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:70
msgid ""
"This is a slider that you can use to quickly change the output black and "
"white ponts."
msgstr "這個滑條可以有效地調整要輸出的色彩的黑白點值。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:71
msgid ""
"These input boxes do the same as the output levels slider, but allow you to "
"finetune the values."
msgstr "這個輸入框的功能和輸出色彩滑條相同，不過你可以透過輸入框來精確地調整數值。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:72
msgid ""
"These buttons allow you to control the visualization of the histogram. The "
"first button makes it use a linear scale (the default). The second one makes "
"it use a logarithmic scale. The third one changes its vertical size to fit "
"the whole histogram in the area. The forth one changes the vertical size to "
"fit in the area most of the histogram but cutting long peaks produced by "
"outliers. You can also change the size of the histogram by clicking and "
"dragging verticaly on the area or by double-clicking to change between \"fit "
"all\" and \"fit cutting long peaks\"."
msgstr ""
"這些按鈕可以操控直方圖的顯示方式。第一個按鈕是線性分佈（預設）；第二個是對數"
"分佈；第三個則是縮放垂直色階分佈圖以符合顯示大小；第四個是縮放大部分的垂直色"
"階分佈圖以符合顯示大小，但是會減去分佈中的峰值。你也可以透過點選及拖曳分佈圖"
"來改變尺寸，雙擊來切換「符合所有」及「符合但減去峰值」。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:73
msgid "This button brings up the auto levels dialog for the current channel."
msgstr "這個按鈕可以自動調整目前色彩通道的色階。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:74
msgid ""
"These buttons allow you to reset (from top to bottom) the levels of the "
"current channel, the input levels of the current channel, the output levels "
"of the current channel, and the levels of all the channels."
msgstr "這些按鈕可以重設（從上至下）目前啟用色彩通道的色階；輸入已啟用通道的色階；輸"
"出已啟用通道的色階；所有通道的色階。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:75
msgid ""
"This button brings up the multi-channel auto levels dialog (only available "
"in the RGBA color model)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:77
msgid ""
"This filter is very useful to do an initial cleanup of scanned lineart or "
"grayscale images. If the scanned lineart is light you can slide the black "
"handle in the input levels to the right to make it darker or if you want to "
"remove the gray areas you can slide the white handle to the left."
msgstr ""
"這個濾鏡可以有效地清理掃瞄的線稿和灰階圖片，如果掃瞄線稿的線條過淡，可以滑動"
"輸入通道黑值的控制柄到右側來把線條加深；或是把白值的控制柄向左滑動來消去灰色"
"的區域。"

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:79
msgid ""
"Auto levels is a quick way to adjust tone of an image. You can update the "
"levels of the filter automaticaly by using the auto levels dialog that "
"appears when clicking one of the buttons explained earlier:"
msgstr "自動色階可以很快地調整影像的色調。點選先前所提到的自動色階按鈕來調整色階："

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:85
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Shadows and Highlights`: In this group of widgets you can select "
"how the shadows and highlights are enhanced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:87
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Method`: this is available only in the RGBA color model when "
"using the multi-channel autolevels and allows you to select if you want to "
"apply the same input levels to all the channels or different input levels to "
"each."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:88
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Shadows clipping` and :guilabel:`Highlights clipping`: these "
"parameters tell the percentage of dark/light colors that are going to be "
"clipped. This is useful when the histogram has long, low valued, tails at "
"the shadows/highlights extremes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:89
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Maximum offset`: this allows to set how much the input black and "
"white points can be moved from their relative extremes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:90
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Shadows color` and :guilabel:`Highlights color`: allows you to "
"choose which colors should be used for the output shadows/highlights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:92
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Midtones`: In this group of widgets you can select how the "
"midtones are enhanced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:94
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Method`: here you can choose not to enhance the midtones or a "
"method to find the midtone point of the image using the median or the mean "
"of the histogram."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:95
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Amount`: with this parameter you can choose how much the final "
"midtone point used to adjust the image differs from the center of the "
"histogram. If you choose 0% then the center of the histogram is used as "
"midtone point (which meand no correction except for the output color). If "
"you choose 100% then the median or mean is used (depending on the method "
"selected). And if you choose a value inbetween then a midtone point between "
"those is used by linearly interpolating them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:96
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Color`: allows you to choose which color should be used for the "
"output midtones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:98
msgid ""
"If you want to change the settings later you can click on the :guilabel:"
"`Create Filter Mask` button to add the levels as a filter mask."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:103
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:100
msgid "Color Adjustment Curves"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:105
msgid ""
"This filter allows you to adjust each channel by manipulating the curves. "
"You can even adjust the alpha channel and the lightness channel through this "
"filter. This is used very often by artists as a post processing filter to "
"slightly heighten the mood of the painting by adjust the overall color. For "
"example a scene with fire breathing dragon may be made more red and yellow "
"by adjusting the curves to give it more warmer look, similarly a snowy "
"mountain scene can be made to look cooler by adjusting the blues and greens. "
"The default shortcut for this filter is :kbd:`Ctrl + M`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:110
msgid "Since 4.1 this filter can also handle Hue and Saturation curves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:117
msgid "Cross-channel color adjustment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:121
msgid ""
"Sometimes, when you are adjusting the colors for an image, you want bright "
"colors to be more saturated, or have a little bit of brightness in the "
"purples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:123
msgid "The Cross-channel color adjustment filter allows you to do this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:125
msgid ""
"At the top, there are two drop-downs. The first one is to choose which :"
"guilabel:`Channel` you wish to modify. The :guilabel:`Driver Channel` drop "
"down is what channel you use to control which parts are modified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:129
msgid ""
"The curve, on the horizontal axis, represents the driver channel, while the "
"vertical axis represent the channel you wish to modify."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:131
msgid ""
"So if you wish to increase the saturation in the lighter parts, you pick :"
"guilabel:`Saturation` in the first drop-down, and :guilabel:`Lightness` as "
"the driver channel. Then, pull up the right end to the top."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:133
msgid ""
"If you wish to desaturate everything but the teal/blues, you select :"
"guilabel:`Saturation` for the channel and :guilabel:`Hue` for the driver. "
"Then put a dot in the middle and pull down the dots on either sides."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:136
msgid "Brightness/Contrast curves"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:138
msgid ""
"This filter allows you to adjust the brightness and contrast of the image by "
"adjusting the curves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:142
msgid ""
"These have been removed in Krita 4.0, because the Color Adjustment filter "
"can do the same. Old files with brightness/contrast curves will be loaded as "
"Color Adjustment curves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:147
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:144
msgid "Color Balance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:149
msgid ""
"This filter allows you to control the color balance of the image by "
"adjusting the sliders for Shadows, Midtones and Highlights. The default "
"shortcut for this filter is :kbd:`Ctrl + B`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:156
msgid "Desaturate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:158
msgid ""
"Image-wide desaturation filter. Will make any image Grayscale. Has several "
"choices by which logic the colors are turned to gray. The default shortcut "
"for this filter is :kbd:`Ctrl + Shift + U`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:163
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:191
msgid "Lightness"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:164
msgid "This will turn colors to gray using the HSL model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:165
msgid "Luminosity (ITU-R BT.709)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:166
msgid ""
"Will turn the color to gray by using the appropriate amount of weighting per "
"channel according to ITU-R BT.709."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:167
msgid "Luminosity (ITU-R BT.601)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:168
msgid ""
"Will turn the color to gray by using the appropriate amount of weighting per "
"channel according to ITU-R BT.601."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:169
msgid "Average"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:170
msgid "Will make an average of all channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:171
msgid "Min"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:172
msgid "Subtracts all from one another to find the gray value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:174
msgid "Max"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:174
msgid "Adds all channels together to get a gray value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:179
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:176
msgid "Invert"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:181
msgid ""
"This filter like the name suggests inverts the color values in the image. So "
"white (1,1,1) becomes black (0,0,0), yellow (1,1,0) becomes blue (0,1,1), "
"etc. The default shortcut for this filter is :kbd:`Ctrl + I`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:187
msgid "Auto Contrast"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:189
msgid "Tries to adjust the contrast to universally acceptable levels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:194
msgid "HSV/HSL Adjustment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:196
msgid ""
"With this filter, you can adjust the Hue, Saturation, Value or Lightness, "
"through sliders. The default shortcut for this filter is :kbd:`Ctrl + U`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:200
msgid "Colorize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:201
msgid ""
"This is an option to have all the pixels have the same hue. It uses a HSL "
"formula by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:203
msgid "Legacy Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:203
msgid ""
"In the development of Krita 4.3, the HSV algorithm was adjusted to maintain "
"the variation in brightness better. This is important because brightness "
"contrast is the most important contrast, so you want to avoid losing "
"variation in it. This option toggles the old behaviour for files made in "
"previous versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:208
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:205
msgid "Threshold"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:210
msgid ""
"A simple black and white threshold filter that uses sRGB luminosity. It'll "
"convert any image to a image with only black and white, with the input "
"number indicating the threshold value at which black becomes white."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:215
msgid "Slope, Offset, Power"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:217
msgid ""
"A different kind of color balance filter, with three color selectors, which "
"will have the same shape as the one used in settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:219
msgid ""
"This filter is particular useful because it has been defined by the American "
"Society for Cinema as \"ASC_CDL\", meaning that it is a standard way of "
"describing a color balance method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:225
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:212
msgid "Slope"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:226
msgid ""
"This represents a multiplication and determine the adjustment of the "
"brighter colors in an image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:227
msgid "Offset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:228
msgid ""
"This determines how much the bottom is offset from the top, and so "
"determines the color of the darkest colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:231
msgid "Power"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/filters/adjust.rst:230
msgid ""
"This represents a power function, and determines the adjustment of the mid-"
"tone to dark colors of an image."
msgstr ""

